article.headline: Monmouth (N.J.) 74, LIU Brooklyn 63
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- Marques Alston scored a game-high 17 points to lead Monmouth to 74-63 win over Long Island on Thursday in the opening round of the Northeast Conference tournament. Alston also had eight rebounds and six assists for the Hawks (15-14), who sealed the win by going five-of-six from the free throw line in the game's closing minutes. Dejan Delic added 15 points for Monmouth, while Chris Kenny had 11 and John Bunch came off the bench to score 10. The Hawks trailed 34-30 at the break, but they took command with a 9-0 run to start the second half. Their defense also frustrated the Blackbirds (12-15), who committed 22 turnovers and hit just 39 percent of their shots. Aubin Scott led Long Island with 13 points and 12 rebounds, while James Williams and Esa Maki-Tulokas also added 13 points and Tyrone Mattison had 12.
